Saint-Gobain Opens Second Plant in Bulgaria, Pari Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   K o n s t a n t i n o v a
-- 
2011-06-02T06:51:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/saint-gobain-opens-second-plant-in-bulgaria-pari-says.html
Cie. de Saint-Gobain SA,  Europe ’s
biggest supplier of building materials, built a second plant in
 Bulgaria ,  Pari  reported, citing Snezhana Simeonova, the manager
of the company’s Bulgarian unit.  The Courbevoie, France-based company invested 6.5 million
lev ($4.8 million) in the new plant near the Black Sea coast,
which has an annual output of 50,000 tonnes, the newspaper said.
Saint-Gobain’s first Bulgarian factory is near the capital Sofia
with an output capacity of 100,000 tonnes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Konstantinova in Sofia at 
 ekonstantino@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
